  <zone type="main">
    <line>And from the waves, sound like delight,</line>
    <line>broke forth</line>
    <line>Harmonizing with solitude; &amp; sent</line>
    <line>Into our heart's aerial merriment;&#8212;</line>
    <line>So as we rode we talked, &amp; the swift thought</line>
    <line>Winging itself with laughter, lingered not</line>
    <line>ours</line>
    <line>But flew from brain to brain, such glee was</line>
    <line>Choorged with light memories of remembered hours</line>
    <line>None deep enought for sadness &#8212; till we came</line>
    <line>Homeward &#8212; whch. always makes the spirits tame</line>
    <line>The day had been cheerful, but cold; &amp; now</line>
    <line>The sun was sinking, &amp; the wind also.&#8212;</line>
    <line>Our talk grew somewhat serious, as may be</line>
    <line>Talk interrupted with such raillery</line>
    <line>As mocks itself, because it cannot scorn</line>
    <line>The thoughts it would extinguish; 'twas</line>
    <line>forlorn</line>
    <line>Yet pleasing, such as once, so poets tell,</line>
  </zone>
